import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='temperature', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of hourly temperature in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['pressure'])
    plt.title('What is the average hourly pressure in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    avg_pressure = sm.stats.DescrStatsW(data['pressure']).mean
    plt.axvline(avg_pressure, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Pressure: {avg_pressure:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
